docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, Nov. 28. -- Uncensored telephone messages from Rio de Janeiro indicate that the federal government has the situation well in hand. The revolt in the northern States had collapsed Tuesday night before the outbreak of yesterday's abortive attempt to spread the uprising to troops in Rio de Janeiro.

docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, Dec. 6. -- Notable increases in exports to the United Kingdom, Canada, Italy, France and Germany were features in the foreign trade of the United States during October. Revised figures on trade with individual countries and grand...
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Dec. 6. -- Notable increases in exports to the United Kingdom, Canada, Italy, France and Germany were features in the foreign trade of the United States during October. Revised figures on trade with individual countries and grand divisions released by the Department of Commerce today placed the total of October exports at $221,237,929 and imports at $189,239,865, with a resulting favorable balance of $31,998,000.
